  "chunk_index": 42,
  "summary": "Following Anthony's deduction regarding the hidden jewels in the library, a tense confrontation erupts between Anthony and the French detective, Lemont. Lemont accuses Anthony of being the criminal Victor King, citing Anthony's presence in South Africa two months prior. Lemont reveals he has requested fingerprint cards and a body size chart from France to compare against Anthony's physical features to prove his identity. Anthony dismisses the accusations, arguing that even if he were Victor King, his past crimes are legally settled or difficult to prove, and he suggests he is merely trying to live a quiet life. Chief Constable Bettlebutt and Lemont further press Anthony, accusing him of fraud regarding Prince Nicolas and involvement in the murder of Prince Michael.\n\nAnthony claims to possess a \"trump card\" in the form of a person he has been keeping upstairs. After a whistle signals from the corridor, Anthony leads the group—including the Earl of Carrington and Lemont—to the library window. Inside, they observe a shadowed figure searching the bookshelves with a flashlight. A violent struggle breaks out, and when the lights are turned on, the group discovers Percy wrestling with a woman. A gunshot rings out, and the woman falls dead. Percy, visibly enraged, declares that the woman killed his master on the orders of the Duke of Michael and claims the gun went off accidentally during their struggle.",
